## Development Guide

### Adding a New Popup Page

1. Create a new Vue component in `src/popup/`
2. Import and use Chrome APIs with TypeScript types
3. Use Vue's Composition API with `<script setup>` for reactive state

Example:
```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import { ref, onMounted } from 'vue';

const data = ref<string>('');

onMounted(() => {
  chrome.storage.local.get(['key'], (result) => {
    data.value = result.key || '';
  });
});
</script>

<template>
  <div>{{ data }}</div>
</template>

<style scoped>
/* Component styles */
</style>
```

### Adding a Content Script

1. Create a new Vue component in `src/content/`
2. Create an entry point that mounts the component to the page
3. Add the script to `manifest.json` content_scripts array

Example:
```vue
<!-- src/content/MyContent.vue -->
<script setup lang="ts">
import { ref } from 'vue';

const visible = ref(true);
</script>

<template>
  <div v-if="visible">Injected content</div>
</template>

<style scoped>
/* Component styles */
</style>
```

```typescript
// src/content/my-content.ts
import { createApp } from 'vue';
import MyContent from './MyContent.vue';

const container = document.createElement('div');
container.id = 'my-extension-content';
document.body.appendChild(container);

createApp(MyContent).mount(container);
```

### Adding a Background Script

Background scripts don't use Vue. Add TypeScript files directly:

```typescript
// src/background/my-handler.ts
chrome.runtime.onMessage.addListener((message, sender, sendResponse) => {
  // Handle messages
  sendResponse({ status: 'ok' });
  return true;
});
```

### Using Chrome APIs

Chrome APIs are fully typed. Import types from the global `chrome` namespace:

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import { ref, onMounted } from 'vue';

const currentTab = ref<chrome.tabs.Tab | null>(null);

onMounted(async () => {
  // Storage API
  const result = await chrome.storage.local.get(['key']);
  console.log(result.key);
  
  await chrome.storage.local.set({ key: 'value' });
  
  // Tabs API
  const tabs = await chrome.tabs.query({ active: true, currentWindow: true });
  currentTab.value = tabs[0];
  
  // Runtime API
  chrome.runtime.sendMessage({ type: 'ACTION' }, (response) => {
    console.log(response);
  });
});
</script>
```

## Customization

### Manifest

Edit `manifest.json` to customize your extension:
- Change name, description, and version
- Add or remove permissions
- Configure content script match patterns
- Update icons and popup settings

### TypeScript Configuration

Edit `tsconfig.json` to customize TypeScript:
- Adjust compiler options
- Add path aliases
- Configure strict mode settings

### Vite Configuration

Edit `vite.config.ts` to customize the build:
- Add Vite plugins
- Configure dev server options
- Modify build optimization settings
- Add path aliases (must match tsconfig.json)

